Zimbabweans have experienced a very rare development where a Cabinet minister, Jonathan Moyo admits he corruptly diverted public funds in order to buy votes. By Kennedy Kaitano,Our ReaderSee also: Carry your own cross, Jonathan Moyo toldMoyo, therefore, by his own admission, has to be quickly arrested and tried for stealing public funds and treating the electorate for purposes of buying votes ahead of the 2018 elections.Infact, Moyo s third crime will be obstructing the course of justice, because for all these years he has been aware of, but has been withholding of the murders and cross border diamond thieves who have ruined our beloved country. Rather that provide the evidence to President Robert Mugabe, police and other necessary organs of the State including the Anti-Corruption Commission, Moyo is avoiding naming the individuals involved in the corrupt practice.